cs.CR, cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as it describes the design and implementation of efficient signature and key-exchange schemes for microcontrollers. It may also belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category as it involves the implementation of cryptographic algorithms on constrained platforms. Additionally, it could be classified under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses the Jacobian point recovery technique. Information Theory (cs.IT) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) are also possible sub-categories as they relate to the efficiency and feasibility of software-only hyperelliptic cryptography on constrained platforms.
